lines.text: RYReynolds
Tobacco Company
Kathy D. Anderson
Regional Promotions Coordinator
Atlanta Regional Operations Unit #2210
3010 Business Park Drive, Suite G
Norcross, GA 30071
January 29, 1997
TO:
Tom Bagby, ROM 2210
RE:
BPE OPPORTUNITIES
Dear Tom:
Listed below are BPE opportunities:
N31 Function Modify Work Plan Using Master List
For each promotion I have to repeatedly change the skus for all our chains. However, since it is to remain consistent for the
calendar year, why can't these only be input once by brand, have Winston-salem capture the information and the requested
skus be used in all future promotions?
Direct Account Payments/TPS
When attempting to issue ist quarter dpc payments in the temporary payment system, I discovered there is no place to pay
for displays. I contacted Sharon Reed on 1/15/97 and she advised me to call Kathryn Noxon. I called Kathryn on 1/16.
Kathryn called me back and ask that i check the screen to see if the display payment was shown because she had voice
mailed Theresa Coleman concerning this problem. I called Kathryn on 1/17, 1/21, 1/22, and 1/24. On 1/24 Kathryn advised
that a program would have to be written and should be available by Friday. The problem that I currently experience with the
missing information is my payments are backing up for direct accounts and we could miss the posting deadline established
by Winston-salem.
Promotion 700031 April Camel B2G2F
In changing the numbers of skus per the sales rep's recommendation, a screen popped up when I did PF5 to update the
changes indicating that our total allocation was 5994, planned 6188, over by 194. I know that you left voice mails in Winston
Salem. No one responded to your voice mails. I personally voice mailed Chris Minner on 1/27/96 (he's out of town) and
Theresa Coleman on 1/29/97. Miriam Smith (1938) 1/29 said reduce 1 sku, PF5 and the system will take, or I could run a
N83 - Non-Vapped Report, remove the skus, then continue to tweak reps figures and if still over allocation contact Sharon
Reid to up allocation. 1/29/97 Sharon Reid called and said that we may have to rob Peter to pay Paul. I told her that I did not
believe we should have skus on non-vapped accounts. Sharon stated that this was a recommendation from Winston-salem
and this should be a management decision to sell these accounts. I told her that I saw skus for Big B who was bought by
Revco and at the present time we could not give them skus until we knew what Revco was going to do with these stores.
Should not have skus listed for non-vapped accounts then we would not encounter this problem, and should not have to
remove skus from non-vapped accounts to balance, very time consuming.
N92 Promotion Posting Report
The above report does not exist under the new N functions. I used the P92 report (old) after each posting to ensure posting
is correct by each direct account now we need an N92 report. On 1/27/97 Sharon Reid advised that this function is not
available and I should contact Chris Minner. I e-mailed Chris Minner on 1/27197.
Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/jjxg0023
